Name: classic pulmonary blastoma
Definition: A carcinosarcoma and embryonal cancer that is located_in embryonic tissue and results_in a mass of rapidly growing cells.

Name: epithelial predominant pulmonary blastoma
Definition: A carcinosarcoma and embryonal cancer that is located_in embryonic tissue and results_in a mass of rapidly growing cells.

Name: pleuropulmonary blastoma
Definition: A pulmonary blastoma that derives_from the lung or pleural cavity.
